### Quarkus REST API Test File
### Environment: http://localhost:8080

@name = "Quarkus Membership API"
@hostname = localhost
@port = 8080

### 1. User Registration
POST {{hostname}}:{{port}}/api/v1/registration
Content-Type: application/json

# Valid registration request
{
  "email": "johndoe@example.com",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### 2. User Login
POST {{hostname}}:{{port}}/api/v1/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "johndoe@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### 3. Get User Profile
GET {{hostname}}:{{port}}/api/v1/profile
Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN_HERE>

### 4. Update User Profile
PUT {{hostname}}:{{port}}/api/v1/profile/update
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN_HERE>

{
  "firstName": "John Updated",
  "lastName": "Doe Updated"
}

### 5. Get All Users (Admin only)
GET {{hostname}}:{{port}}/api/v1/users
Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN_HERE>

### 6. Swagger UI Documentation
GET {{hostname}}:{{port}}/swagger-ui

### 7. OpenAPI Specification
GET {{hostname}}:{{port}}/openapi

### 8. Health Check
GET {{hostname}}:{{port}}/api/v1/health

### 9. Application Info
GET {{hostname}}:{{port}}/api/v1/info